Kwara State Governor, Alhaji Abdulfatah Ahmed on Friday visited some victims of Offa robbery incident who were on admission at the General Hospital, Ilorin. The governor, who was escorted round the hospital wards by staff and medical personnel, also visited the University of Ilorin Teaching Hospital (UITH). Governor Ahmed promised to foot the medical bills of the injured who were hospitalized at all the hospitals visited. He also assured that his administration will improve governmentâ€™s support for security agencies in the state to nip crimes in the bud.  